Explain about Functional and Non-Functional Testing. In which scenario u would choose non functional testing?

Functional Testing:
Unit Testing: Testing individual components or modules of the software in isolation to ensure they function 
correctly.
Integration Testing.
System Testing.
Acceptance Testing (UAT - User Acceptance Testing): 
Re-Testing.
Regression Testing.
Smoke Testing:(Build Verification Testing).
Sanity Testing.
2. Non-Functional Testing:
Performance Testing.
Load Testing
Stress Testing.
Scalability Testing.
Security Testing.
Usability Testing.
Compatibility Testing.
Reliability Testing.
Accessibility Testing.

I would choose non-functional testing when performance, security, scalability, usability, or reliability are critical to the business,
such as in banking, e-commerce, or high-traffic applications.
